==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ideo-motor
<hw>I`de*o-mo"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ideo-</ets> + <ets>motor</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Applied to those actions, or muscular movements, which are
automatic expressions of dominant ideas, rather than the result of
distinct volitional efforts, as the act of expressing the thoughts in
speech, or in writing, while the mind is occupied in the composition of
the sentence.</def> <rj><au>Carpenter.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

